zujkomiller.genetic
Class GenerationProducer

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--zujkomiller.genetic.GenerationProducer
Direct Known Subclasses:
FixedBagProducer, FixedSetProducer, VariableBagProducer, VariableSetProducer
public abstract class GenerationProducer
extends java.lang.Object

Subclasses of GenerationProducer are responsible for creating an initial population of Chromosomes, and then for creating a child Generation from a parent Generation by replicating the best individuals from the parent, dropping the worst individuals, performing crossovers, and performing mutations.

doReplications

protected abstract Chromosome[] doReplications(Chromosome[] parent)
Use numToReplicate and numOfReplicationsEach to copy the top scorers in the parent generation into the child generation.
Parameters:
The - parent generation from which to create the child generation.
Returns:
The child generation created from the parent, with the top scorers in the parent replicated in the child and the bottom scorers in the parent removed from the child.

doCrossovers

protected abstract void doCrossovers(Chromosome[] nextGen)
Modify the nextGen passed in as a parameter by performing crossovers on some of the Chromosomes. Use crossOversPerGen to determine how many crossovers to perform.
